28:13.859 --> 28:18.096
‐ Yeah‐‐well,
I used to ski, like, a lot.

28:18.096 --> 28:19.731
I wanted to go
to the Olympics,

28:19.731 --> 28:22.201
so finished second
in the worlds

28:22.201 --> 28:25.537
and then 2006 I went to Torino.

28:27.105 --> 28:29.775
And then this happened.
‐ How did you do that?

28:29.775 --> 28:32.244
‐ Well, it was
my second mogul run.

28:33.912 --> 28:35.047
I heard my knee pop.

28:35.047 --> 28:36.715
It was before the jump,
and I couldn't stop,

28:36.715 --> 28:40.819
and I landed, and I heard
a bunch of bones crack.

28:40.819 --> 28:42.621
I could see my tib fib
sticking out

28:42.621 --> 28:44.423
of my competition suit.

28:44.423 --> 28:48.527
They said I could have
lost my leg or even died.

28:49.361 --> 28:50.929
Whew, fun day.

28:52.631 --> 28:54.433
‐ Couldn't stop?
‐ Yeah.

28:55.667 --> 28:58.971
‐ Almost died.
‐ Yeah.

28:58.971 --> 29:00.906
‐ That's great.

29:00.906 --> 29:02.708
‐ So I found
a new perspective‐‐

29:02.708 --> 29:06.378
‐ I've got to go.
‐ We're not done eating.

29:06.378 --> 29:09.448
That's where it usually ends.
[sighs]

29:09.448 --> 29:12.384
‐ Aw, another date night
just you and a hot dog?

29:12.384 --> 29:13.685
‐ Actually, I have two.

29:13.685 --> 29:14.987
You could have
one for each hand

29:14.987 --> 29:16.121
just like in high school.

29:16.121 --> 29:17.356
‐ I learned
that trick from you.

29:17.356 --> 29:18.624
‐ All right, slut.
‐ Hoe bag.

29:18.624 --> 29:20.025
‐ Want to bowl?
‐ Yeah.

29:20.025 --> 29:21.326
‐ Let's do it.

29:22.361 --> 29:25.297
[soft dramatic music]

29:25.297 --> 29:32.471
♪ ♪

29:46.151 --> 29:48.387
‐ The kid has to ride
his bike down this hill

29:48.387 --> 29:49.721
on the way to school.

29:49.721 --> 29:52.658
Without brakes,
he'll never survive.

29:52.658 --> 29:54.059
It's a good feeling
to know

29:54.059 --> 29:56.028
I am the smartest person
on Earth‐‐ugh!

29:56.028 --> 29:57.162
[car horn honks]

29:57.162 --> 29:59.498
‐ Get out of the street,
you idiot!

29:59.498 --> 30:03.001
♪ ♪

30:03.001 --> 30:04.770
‐ Sorry.

30:05.771 --> 30:06.772
Hm.

30:12.377 --> 30:12.978
‐ I liked Sam,
but he was always,

30:14.046 --> 30:15.881
"Don't eat this.
Don't eat that.

30:15.881 --> 30:17.349
Your diet's gonna kill you."

30:17.349 --> 30:19.318
‐ Well, what you eat
is important.

30:19.318 --> 30:22.688
‐ [chuckles strangely]
I don't agree with that.

30:22.688 --> 30:24.156
‐ Oh, no?

30:24.156 --> 30:26.024
‐ No, there are
ten things on here

30:26.024 --> 30:27.459
that are going
to kill him sooner

30:27.459 --> 30:29.761
than eating bad food does.
‐ Harry.

30:29.761 --> 30:33.632
‐ No, I want to hear.
Sam never mentioned that.

30:33.632 --> 30:35.133
Tell me when.

30:36.768 --> 30:41.640
Look, I just turned 80.
You can give it to me straight.

30:41.640 --> 30:43.542
How long do you think I have?

30:43.542 --> 30:46.311
‐ Do you like Christmas?
‐ Yes, very much.

30:46.311 --> 30:48.480
‐ Celebrate it before June.

30:48.480 --> 30:50.248
‐ Oh, okay.

30:51.883 --> 30:53.218
Oh.

30:53.218 --> 30:56.355
But between now and Christmas?

30:57.823 --> 31:00.359
‐ You can eat
anything you want.

31:02.027 --> 31:04.496
‐ I like you.
[chuckles]

31:04.496 --> 31:06.064
This is the first time
that a doctor's

31:06.064 --> 31:08.734
been totally honest with me.

31:08.734 --> 31:12.270
This town is very lucky to have
a doctor as good as you.

31:12.270 --> 31:14.172
‐ Yes, you are lucky.

31:15.974 --> 31:18.143
‐ You certainly have
a particular style.

31:18.143 --> 31:20.779
That's impressive.
He doesn't like anyone.

31:20.779 --> 31:23.348
‐ Ben Hawthorne's here.
There's been an accident.

31:23.348 --> 31:25.917
‐ An accident?
‐ Yeah.

31:27.552 --> 31:31.656
‐ Hello, Mayor Hawthorne.
I'm sorry for your loss.

31:31.656 --> 31:33.859
‐ Uh, what loss?

31:33.859 --> 31:35.260
[upbeat music]

31:35.260 --> 31:37.095
This little guy fell
on his bike in the driveway.

31:37.095 --> 31:38.997
I think he's
gonna need stitches.

31:38.997 --> 31:44.102
♪ ♪

31:44.102 --> 31:45.203
Come on.
‐ Okay.

31:45.203 --> 31:47.339
‐ Stitches‐‐stitches,
that's it?

31:47.339 --> 31:49.441
‐ Don't sound
so disappointed, weirdo.

31:49.441 --> 31:52.544
♪ ♪

31:55.514 --> 31:56.648
‐ It's okay, buddy.

31:56.648 --> 31:59.151
I'll be here right next
to you the whole time.

31:59.151 --> 32:01.286
‐ You're, like, 600 feet away.

32:01.286 --> 32:03.221
‐ Yeah, well, I don't want
to get in the doctor's way.

32:03.221 --> 32:06.625
See, just stay strong,
okay, pal?

32:08.059 --> 32:09.961
‐ Thank you, nurse.

32:12.898 --> 32:16.668
I hear you had a little
bike accident this morning‐‐

32:16.668 --> 32:18.303
very little.

32:21.573 --> 32:23.442
Your son is very shy.

32:25.544 --> 32:28.146
You can look at me, Max.
I don't bite.

32:28.146 --> 32:30.782
[whispers]
Actually, I do.

32:30.782 --> 32:32.551
[snarls]

32:35.587 --> 32:38.089
You're lucky your brakes
failed on the driveway

32:38.089 --> 32:39.591
and not on the main road.

32:39.591 --> 32:41.359
This should have been
a lot worse.

32:43.328 --> 32:46.031
‐ How did you know
it was my brakes?

32:47.432 --> 32:49.568
‐ I just assumed.

32:49.568 --> 32:53.638
We get a lot
of failed brake accidents‐‐

32:53.638 --> 32:55.740
all kinds,

32:55.740 --> 33:00.312
cars, wheelchairs, boats.

33:00.312 --> 33:01.713
‐ Mm, can we hurry this up?

33:01.713 --> 33:04.049
That smell of gauze
is just something else.

33:04.049 --> 33:05.650
[soft dramatic music]

33:05.650 --> 33:08.553
‐ Luckily, we have Novocain
for good boys.

33:08.553 --> 33:12.390
I can numb this up,
and you won't feel a thing.

33:12.390 --> 33:15.927
So tell me, Max,
are you going to be

33:15.927 --> 33:18.930
a good boy?

33:18.930 --> 33:20.665
‐ Of course.

33:20.665 --> 33:22.901
♪ ♪

33:22.901 --> 33:26.037
[whispers]
No, never.

33:27.639 --> 33:30.308
‐ Well, then I have my answer.

33:30.308 --> 33:33.345
Let's put in
a couple of stitches.

33:33.345 --> 33:35.146
‐ Go right ahead.

33:35.146 --> 33:38.116
[upbeat music]

33:38.116 --> 33:41.953
♪ ♪

33:41.953 --> 33:44.489
‐ [groans]
‐ How is it, Max?

33:44.489 --> 33:46.725
‐ It's fine.

33:46.725 --> 33:48.026
Is there a mosquito in here?

33:48.026 --> 33:51.329
'Cause I think I just got
a tiny bite on my arm.

33:51.329 --> 33:53.632
‐ This is deeper
than I thought.

33:53.632 --> 33:55.567
We might need three stitches.

33:55.567 --> 33:57.669
‐ How about five?

33:57.669 --> 34:03.475
♪ ♪

34:03.475 --> 34:06.645
‐ [snarls]

34:06.645 --> 34:13.385
♪ ♪

34:13.385 --> 34:16.454
Well, I guess that's it.
‐ Really?

34:16.454 --> 34:19.658
I didn't feel anything.
‐ Huh, good for you.

34:19.658 --> 34:21.793
I did.
Okay, let's go.

34:21.793 --> 34:23.128
‐ Yes, yes.

34:23.128 --> 34:24.296
‐ Remember,
if you're not careful,

34:24.296 --> 34:26.665
something horrible
can happen to you.

34:26.665 --> 34:29.734
‐ Oh, don't worry.
I can take care of myself.

34:29.734 --> 34:31.903
By the way, your shoe's untied.

34:32.771 --> 34:34.372
Made you look, you dummy.

34:35.874 --> 34:37.609
Wait, I‐‐look!

34:37.609 --> 34:41.079
It‐‐it is untied,

34:41.079 --> 34:44.149
so ha, ha, ha!

34:45.417 --> 34:46.952
[Raye Zaragoza's
"In the River"]

34:46.952 --> 34:50.422
♪ ♪

34:50.422 --> 34:51.523
‐ [sighs]

34:51.523 --> 34:53.592
‐ I know Sam
and you were close.

34:53.592 --> 34:56.394
There are things
you can do that will help you.

34:56.394 --> 34:59.564
You could cut your hair
to honor the deceased.

34:59.564 --> 35:01.032
‐ I can handle it.

35:01.032 --> 35:02.767
♪ ♪

35:02.767 --> 35:05.937
Maybe you should start
letting me live my own life.

35:05.937 --> 35:08.006
Worrying about
every man I meet,

35:08.006 --> 35:10.175
making me dinner every night‐‐

35:10.175 --> 35:12.010
I'm not 16 anymore.

35:13.912 --> 35:15.814
Mm, it's okay.

35:15.814 --> 35:18.350
The dinner part is nice.

35:18.350 --> 35:20.619
‐ If you were 16,
you wouldn't even be here.

35:20.619 --> 35:21.820
You'd be in Denver.

35:21.820 --> 35:24.556
‐ Oh.
[laughs]

35:24.556 --> 35:26.524
Good one.

35:26.524 --> 35:27.759
Now that I live at home,

35:27.759 --> 35:29.461
you're gonna start
being my father?

35:29.461 --> 35:32.063
‐ Well, you never
stopped being my daughter.

35:32.063 --> 35:38.370
♪ ♪

35:38.370 --> 35:40.972
I hope you're this upset
when I die.

35:40.972 --> 35:43.074
‐ Jesus, Dad.

35:43.074 --> 35:49.547
‐ ♪ There's gotta be
some hope ♪

35:49.547 --> 35:51.983
♪ ♪

35:51.983 --> 35:55.987
♪ There's gotta be some hope ♪

35:55.987 --> 35:59.491
♪ ♪

35:59.491 --> 36:03.662
♪ There's gotta be some way ♪

36:03.662 --> 36:07.966
♪ For you to send
your dogs away ♪

36:07.966 --> 36:10.802
♪ And to leave
the land alone ♪

36:10.802 --> 36:17.909
♪ ♪

36:19.144 --> 36:23.715
♪ It's gotta be a crime ♪

36:23.715 --> 36:26.685
♪ ♪

36:26.685 --> 36:30.789
♪ Somewhere in your heart,
you'll find ♪

36:30.789 --> 36:34.325
♪ ♪

36:34.325 --> 36:38.863
♪ We're fighting
for our right ♪

36:38.863 --> 36:42.500
♪ To keep the future bright ♪

36:42.500 --> 36:45.570
♪ And protect
the ones we love ♪

36:45.570 --> 36:52.544
♪ ♪

36:54.412 --> 36:58.349
♪ In the river is our sisters
and our brothers ♪

36:58.349 --> 37:01.553
♪ ♪

37:01.553 --> 37:05.623
♪ We are camping out
for each other ♪

37:05.623 --> 37:12.530
♪ ♪

37:15.734 --> 37:18.937
‐ Did you burn your scrubs
from the other night?

37:18.937 --> 37:20.371
‐ No.

37:20.371 --> 37:21.840
♪ ♪

37:21.840 --> 37:23.374
‐ You know you should.

37:23.374 --> 37:26.277
You've got to release
Sam's spirit from this world.

37:26.277 --> 37:29.914
Otherwise, he'll linger.
‐ I know.

37:29.914 --> 37:33.618
♪ ♪

37:39.691 --> 37:40.458
[Raye Zaragoza's
"Bushwick Avenue"]

37:42.293 --> 37:49.434
♪ ♪

37:51.603 --> 37:54.339
‐ ♪ I've been
thinking about you ♪

37:54.339 --> 37:55.673
[car horn honks]

37:55.673 --> 37:56.641
‐ Shut up!

37:56.641 --> 37:59.043
‐ ♪ Been thinking about you ♪

37:59.043 --> 38:04.616
♪ ♪

38:04.616 --> 38:08.720
♪ I've been taking
my time with you ♪

38:08.720 --> 38:12.123
♪ Been taking
my time with you ♪

38:12.123 --> 38:14.926
♪ But falling quickly too ♪

38:14.926 --> 38:16.795
♪ ♪

38:16.795 --> 38:20.565
♪ And sometimes
how I lose my mind ♪

38:20.565 --> 38:24.335
♪ When I am feeling fine ♪

38:24.335 --> 38:27.939
♪ Since I have been with you ♪

38:27.939 --> 38:29.407
♪ ♪

38:29.407 --> 38:34.412
♪ Was 14 straight into 1,013 ♪

38:34.412 --> 38:36.681
‐ [knocks]
‐ Hey.

38:36.681 --> 38:38.116
‐ Hey.

38:38.116 --> 38:45.290
♪ ♪

38:47.058 --> 38:49.627
Mrs. McGill has a crush on you.

38:49.627 --> 38:51.596
‐ [chuckles]
It's not a crush.

38:51.596 --> 38:53.231
She's 90
and comes in every week

38:53.231 --> 38:55.033
because she's a hypochondriac.

38:55.033 --> 38:58.002
♪ ♪

38:58.002 --> 39:00.271
Hey.
‐ Uh‐huh?

39:00.271 --> 39:01.840
‐ A little gin rummy?

39:01.840 --> 39:04.142
‐ Oh...

39:04.142 --> 39:06.377
I'm gonna have
to take a raincheck.

39:06.377 --> 39:08.379
Big day tomorrow.

39:08.379 --> 39:11.449
Oh, but I'll beat you
next time.

39:11.449 --> 39:14.285
‐ You wish.
‐ [chuckles]

39:14.285 --> 39:19.424
♪ ♪

39:24.929 --> 39:26.731
‐ There's no one sitting there.

39:30.835 --> 39:32.804
‐ Dan's not my real father.

39:34.839 --> 39:37.075
My mom left when I was one.

39:37.075 --> 39:39.043
Dan took me in,
and he raised me.

39:39.043 --> 39:40.578
He gave me everything.

39:43.348 --> 39:45.650
But I never really felt
like I fit in.

39:47.118 --> 39:50.221
Sam was the only one
I could talk to about all that.

39:52.857 --> 39:55.360
I never should have left
that night he died.

39:55.360 --> 39:58.663
I was tired.
I just wanted to go home.

40:03.034 --> 40:04.435
He was always there for me.

40:04.435 --> 40:06.337
I should have
been there for him.

40:07.405 --> 40:09.240
‐ He was poisoned.

40:09.240 --> 40:11.209
You couldn't have helped him.
‐ Maybe.

40:12.577 --> 40:14.579
At least he wouldn't
have died alone.

40:20.618 --> 40:22.787
‐ Do you want
to play a card game?

40:25.223 --> 40:26.724
‐ Yeah.

40:28.159 --> 40:29.460
Thanks.
‐ Okay.

40:29.460 --> 40:31.863
I'll put my stuff in my office.

40:33.932 --> 40:35.967
‐ This is your office now.

40:35.967 --> 40:39.003
[tender music]

40:39.003 --> 40:45.944
♪ ♪

40:50.248 --> 40:52.150
‐ I did not want
to play cards,

40:52.150 --> 40:53.785
but I knew Asta wanted to.

40:53.785 --> 40:59.424
♪ ♪

40:59.424 --> 41:01.693
She was sad.
I could feel it.

41:01.693 --> 41:03.494
♪ ♪

41:03.494 --> 41:05.563
I should not be able
to feel an emotion

41:05.563 --> 41:07.432
that is inside somebody else.

41:07.432 --> 41:08.833
♪ ♪

41:08.833 --> 41:11.836
[dramatic music]

41:11.836 --> 41:18.743
♪ ♪

41:34.025 --> 41:41.199
♪ ♪

41:42.600 --> 41:43.534
[sighs]

41:46.170 --> 41:48.139
Tellurium.

41:48.139 --> 41:51.843
♪ ♪

41:51.843 --> 41:56.814
I know that they are all
connected by these feelings,

41:56.814 --> 41:58.683
these emotions...

41:58.683 --> 42:03.855
♪ ♪

42:03.855 --> 42:06.290
Feelings of devotion...

42:06.290 --> 42:08.893
♪ ♪

42:08.893 --> 42:10.895
Sadness...

42:10.895 --> 42:13.698
♪ ♪

42:13.698 --> 42:15.066
Love.

42:15.066 --> 42:17.668
‐ In Greek mythology,
there exists this legend...

42:17.668 --> 42:19.837
♪ ♪

42:19.837 --> 42:23.107
‐ Maybe I am more connected
to them now

42:23.107 --> 42:25.443
I had an emptiness
that no amount of potato chips

42:25.443 --> 42:27.345
or hot dogs would cure,

42:27.345 --> 42:29.180
but when I found
the tellurium,

42:29.180 --> 42:31.149
the ache went away.

42:31.149 --> 42:32.717
It wasn't coming
from my stomach.

42:32.717 --> 42:35.653
It was coming from my heart.

42:35.653 --> 42:38.890
Human emotions
are growing inside of me.

42:38.890 --> 42:42.727
I think the one I feel now
they call lonely.

42:42.727 --> 42:45.997
♪ ♪

42:45.997 --> 42:49.434
In the same way Asta
misses Sam Hodges,

42:49.434 --> 42:53.271
I miss my planet, my people.

42:53.271 --> 42:54.872
But having found
the tellurium,

42:54.872 --> 42:57.575
I can finally
heal my broken heart

42:57.575 --> 42:59.377
because, once I
detonate my device

42:59.377 --> 43:02.780
and fry every human being
on Earth,

43:02.780 --> 43:05.483
I can fly home.

43:06.918 --> 43:09.387
Now I just need
to find my device

43:09.387 --> 43:11.089
without being discovered.

43:11.089 --> 43:14.058
[soft dramatic music]

43:14.058 --> 43:21.165
♪ ♪

43:28.139 --> 43:31.109
[suspenseful music]

43:31.109 --> 43:37.882
♪ ♪
